OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sat 11 Jul to Mon 20 Jul
OL,6,FSouthern areas are likely to start
OL,7,Fthis period hot, with heatwave
OL,8,Fconditions persisting. To the north,
OL,9,Fan Atlantic frontal zone will
OL,10,Fintroduce somewhat cooler conditions,
OL,11,Fwith the potential for scattered
OL,12,Fthunderstorms to develop just ahead of
OL,13,Fthis. Into the following week, high
OL,14,Fpressure is likely to build to the
OL,15,Fnorth or northwest of the UK, though
OL,16,Fits exact orientation is rather more
OL,17,Funcertain. This would bring a lot of
OL,18,Fdry weather for many areas, though
OL,19,Fperhaps an increased chance,
OL,20,Frelatively to previous days, of
OL,21,Fshowers or thunderstorms in the south.
OL,22,FTemperatures probably moderating a
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Flittle, though remaining above average
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Ffor many areas.
